Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

User architectural critique: 'stop treating filing frequency as signal
strength. Frequent amendments often create noise, while the real edge
comes from detecting the first definitive catalyst and then tracking only
the next key milestone.'

Transforms the module from RSS-aggregator + keyword-classifier into
event-intelligence pipeline.

NEW: lib/news/event-intelligence.ts (~340 lines)

  EVENT TYPES (20):
    TENDER_OFFER · GOING_PRIVATE · MERGER_RECOMMENDATION · MERGER_DEFINITIVE
    SPIN_OFF · OPEN_OFFER · BUYBACK_TENDER · BUYBACK_OPEN_MARKET
    BONUS_ISSUE · STOCK_SPLIT · DIVIDEND_HIKE · RIGHTS_ISSUE
    QIP_PLACEMENT · DEMERGER_INDIA · IPO_SUBSIDIARY
    TURNAROUND_OPERATING · TURNAROUND_NARRATIVE · STAKE_SALE
    ACQUISITION_PUBLIC · NEWS_RUMOR · UNCLASSIFIED

  FORM-STRICT CLASSIFIER (replaces keyword detection):
    Layer 1 — SEC form codes (deterministic):
      SC TO-T / SC TO-I → TENDER_OFFER
      SC 13E-3          → GOING_PRIVATE
      SC 14D-9          → MERGER_RECOMMENDATION
      S-4               → MERGER_DEFINITIVE
      10-12B / 10-12G   → SPIN_OFF
    Layer 2 — India / general headline patterns
      open offer / NCLT scheme / bonus issue / dividend hike / etc.

  CANONICAL EVENT ID:
    sha1(event_type + ticker_or_target).slice(0,12)
    All amendments + media coverage of the SAME deal collapse to ONE event.
    SC TO-I/A x3 + SC TO-I (original) = ONE CanonicalEvent with
    amendment_count=3, not 4 separate news items.

  QUANTITATIVE CATALYST SCORING (per user spec):
    +30  definitive filing (non-amendment + form-based event type)
    +20  named listed ticker
    +15  explicit deadline (record date / tender expiry / by DATE)
    +15  deal consideration disclosed ($X / Rs X / per share / spread)
    +10  spread/stub value calculable
    -20  amendment-only filing
    -15  fund / closed-end housekeeping
    -10  no primary-source link (SEC / exchange / press release)
    Then × decay multiplier with event-type half-life:
      SPIN_OFF / DEMERGER / IPO_SUBSIDIARY  = 90d
      MERGER / TENDER / GOING_PRIVATE       = 30d
      BUYBACK / RIGHTS / QIP                = 14d
      TURNAROUND_OPERATING                  = 21d
      TURNAROUND_NARRATIVE / RUMOR          = 5d

  TRADABILITY FILTER:
    Hard reject: fund-only events (Bow River / Brookfield Infra Income etc.)
    Hard reject: amendment without primary filing in window
    Hard reject: rumour / unclassified
    TIER_1: hard catalyst + named ticker + primary source + decay >= 20
    TIER_2: hard catalyst missing one of above
    WATCHLIST: dividends / bonus / capital allocation / turnaround narrative
    NOISE: rejected

  AUTO-GENERATED 'WHY TRADABLE' BLOCK per event type:
    what_happened / what_matters / what_to_watch / what_breaks_thesis
    Per-event-type templates (TENDER_OFFER mentions tender expiry +
    proration; SPIN_OFF mentions index-fund forced selling window;
    DEMERGER_INDIA mentions NCLT effective date + debt allocation; etc.)

  LIFECYCLE STAGE:
    rumor → announced → amended → approved → closed

WIRED INTO route.ts buildFeed():
  After existing FeedItem dedupe + 90-day rolling cache:
    Step 1: extract event signals per item
    Step 2: bucket by canonical event ID (skip UNCLASSIFIED noise)
    Step 3: pick primary_filing = earliest non-amendment SEC.gov item
    Step 4: amendments = all /A filings in the bucket
    Step 5: score catalyst with decay
    Step 6: classify tradability
    Step 7: generate why_tradable
    Step 8: sort by tier desc, then decay_score desc

  Response shape EXTENDED (back-compat preserved):
    by_category — old shape, unchanged
    events     — NEW: CanonicalEvent[] with full institutional treatment
    by_tier    — NEW: { TIER_1, TIER_2, WATCHLIST, NOISE } counts

FRONTEND (page.tsx):
  Type definition added so the page can read canonical events.
  Full rendering switch to canonical events follows in 0105b.

Type-check clean.
